# Language & Style

## English only

All of the following must be written in **English**:

- Source code identifiers (classes, methods, variables)
- Comments and docstrings
- Commit messages and PR descriptions
- README and documentation
- Log messages and exception text
- Test names and assertion messages
- Shell script output (except allowed symbols below)

User-facing chat with the developer may stay in their preferred language; **codebase content is always English**.

## No emojis in code

Do **not** use emojis in:

- Comments, log lines, print statements, test output, README technical sections

**Allowed only:**

- Checkmark: `✓` or `[x]` for pass/success indicators
- X mark: `✗` for fail/error indicators

### BAD

```java
// 🚀 Starting transfer...
log.info("💰 Transfer complete!");
```

### GOOD

```java
// Settles a matched trade between buyer and seller accounts.
log.info("Transfer complete: transferId={}", transferId);
```

```bash
echo "✓ PostgreSQL accepts connections"
echo "✗ Redis did not respond"
```
